A work area can be of type "Tool" or "Person" and have a specific Work Center Group Code.

The other fields are filled in in the same way as classic work centers.

<img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000617-0/2ManufacturingBaseToolkit-ENU.png"><br>

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| Type | Person: allows you to define the employment and hours of work of the personnel working on a machine (e.g. personnel dealing with painting)<br> Tool: allows you to define the machinery used for processing (e.g. a frame for painting) <br> Machine: not used |